    Name: "Datatypes in Python - Numeric Datatype",
    To: "/videos/python-course/python-4",
    desc: "In this video, I have shown you what Datatypes actually is and have discussed some numeric datatypes in Python",
    Categories: "Python",
    Sno: "4",
    Iframe: "https://www.youtube.com/embed/V8_vZxSmzQw",
    content: <><h4>Datatypes in Python</h4>Datatypes means the types of data that we store in a variable<br />Types of Datatypes in Python<ul><li>Numeric</li><li>Sequence</li><li>Boolean</li><li>None</li><li>Dictionary or Maps</li><li>Sets</li></ul><h5>Numeric Datatype</h5>Numeric Datatype is divided into three types<ul><li>Int</li><li>Float</li><li>Complex</li></ul><h5>Sequence Datatype</h5>Sequence Datatype is divided into three types<ul><li>Strings</li><li>List</li><li>Tuple</li></ul><h4>None Datatype</h4>None Datatype are the type of data which contain Nothing<br />You can assign any variable to None by just writng the variable name and None seperating with equal to sign (=)<PrismCode code="a = None" language="python" /><h4>Numeric Datatypes</h4><h5>Int</h5>Int datatypes are the type of data which contain integer like -12, 84, 23, etc..<br />You can assign any variable to int with the variable name and any Integers seperating with equal to sign (=)<PrismCode code={`a = 233\nprint(type(a))`} language="python" /><h6>Determining the Datatype of any variable</h6>To determing the datatype of any variable we use type() function where we have to write the variable name in the parantheses <p></p><h5>Float</h5>Float datatypes are the type of data which contain decimal value like -12.8, 84.6, 23.94, etc..<br />You can assign any variable to float with the variable name and any decimal value seperating with equal to sign (=) <PrismCode code={`a = 233.34\nprint(type(a))`} language="python" /><br /><h5>Complex</h5>Complex Datatypes are the type of Data like in Maths we have complex number which represented as a + bi<PrismCode code={`a = 3+4j\nprint(type(a))`} language="python" /><br />Where a is the real number and bi is the imaginary part and i = underoot -1<br />In python we have a + bj where a is real number and bj is imaginary part and j = underoot -1 <p></p><h4>Calculations with Numeric Datatype</h4>We can do any type of Calculations with the Numeric Datatype<br />To do so :<br />We have to write print() function under parenthese we have to write the Calculation without quotes<PrismCode code={`a = 84\nb = 85\nprint(a + b)\nprint(a - b)\nprint(a * b)\nprint(a / b)`} language="python" /><h5>Source Code</h5><PrismCode code={`# int or integer value\na = 89\nprint(a)\nprint(a + 89)\n\n# float or decimal value\nnum1 = 2.1\nprint(type(num1))\nprint(num1 // 10)\n\n# complex type\n\nnum1 = 3 + 4j\nnum2 = 6 + 8j\n\nprint(num1 / num2)`} language="python" /></>
