    content: <>Tuples are used to store multiple items in a single variable.<br />Syntax to make tuples in python<PrismCode language="python" code={`a = ("apple", "banana", "cherry")\n\nprint(a)\nprint(type(a)) # when you run it you will see <class 'Tuples'>`} /><h5>Tuples are immutable</h5>Tuples are immutable because we can't change the items of the tuples where we can change the items in Lists<p></p>More on <a href="https://www.w3schools.com/python/python_tuples.asp" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">tuples</a><h5>Source Code</h5><PrismCode language="python" code={`a = (89, "tuple", 69)\nprint(a)\nprint(type(a))\nprint(a[0])`} /></>
