    Iframe: "https://www.youtube.com/embed/3THcWVVSXe8",
    content: <>Boolean Datatypes are the type of Data which include the <b>True</b> or <b>False</b> like:<br />-34 is greter than 54 - <b>False</b><br />33 is lesser than 53 - <b>True</b><br />33 is equal to 34 - 1 - <b>True</b><br />etc.<br /><br />In python we say this kind of logic is called boolean. So, to do so in python we use bool() function like This<br />Now if you want to make a variable contains boolean dataypes. like this: -<PrismCode language="python" code={`print(bool(87876 > 87)) # the output is <b>True</b>\nprint(bool 34 == 35 - 1) # we use double equals to when we want to use equal to in the boolean statements`} /><br /><h5>Calculations of boolean Datatypes</h5>If you heared about binary language which is a computer language. There are only two numbers in binary language which are 0, 1<br /><br />Where 0 is False and 1 is True, So, By Knowing this you can know how the Calculations works of boolean datatype like if you make the variable like this: <br /><br />Now if you want to calculate like print(a + b) the operation is like this <b>the value of a is False and which is 0</b> and <b>b is True or 1</b> now if you want to add a + b which is <b>0 + 1</b> which equals to 1-<br /><br /><b>Like this you can do substraction, multiply and divide the boolean Datatypes</b><PrismCode language="python" code={`a = 34 > 56 # returns False or 0\nprint(a)\nb = 3434 == 3436 - 2 # returns True or 1\nprint(b)\na = 34 > 56 # returns False or 0\nprint(a)\n\nb = 3434 == 3436 - 2 # returns True or 1\nprint(a + b) # returns 1`} /></>
